%==============================================================================
\chapter{AutoGluon Ensemble}
\label{ch:autogluon}
%==============================================================================

\section{Overview}

AutoGluon (\texttt{09C\_AutoGluon.py}) complements the hand-tuned XGBoost by 
automatically selecting and ensembling LightGBM, XGBoost, CatBoost, 
Random Forest, ExtraTrees, and Neural Networks. The implementation uses 
\texttt{good\_quality} preset with a 3,600-second time limit per Stage 1 run.

\section{Two-Stage Implementation}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Stage 1 — Full training:} AutoGluon trains on all training rows 
    (1998--2010), using years 2011--2015 as a holdout for model selection. 
    The best ensemble is retrained on train + holdout combined (\texttt{\_FULL} suffix). 
    Produces the deployable model.
    
    \item \textbf{Stage 2 — Manual expanding window CV:} Three sequential AutoGluon fits 
    (Folds 2/3/4, 900 seconds each, \texttt{medium\_quality} preset) produce honest 
    out-of-fold CV predictions for AP comparison with XGBoost.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Best Ensemble Composition}

