\section{Individual Model Hyperparameters and Performance}

The \texttt{good\_quality} preset trains 11 distinct model configurations.
Their hyperparameters and holdout AP scores for M3 (raw features) are shown below —
this is the most informative setting as it has the largest feature space and 
the clearest performance differentiation between model families.

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{AutoGluon Individual Model Hyperparameters and Holdout AP — M3 (Raw Features)}
\rowcolors{2}{gray!10}{white}
\small
\begin{tabular}{lrp{8.5cm}}
\toprule
\textbf{Model} & \textbf{Holdout AP} & \textbf{Key Hyperparameters} \\
\midrule
LightGBMLarge    & 0.6972 & lr=0.03, num\_leaves=128, feature\_fraction=0.9, min\_data\_in\_leaf=3, rounds=4,687 \\
LightGBMXT       & 0.6848 & lr=0.05, extra\_trees=True, rounds=1,855 \\
